summary: People ™️ of Internet have been getting on my nerves lately. Let's dive in. I was looking for Captain Marvel analysis on YouTube...
body:
People ™️ of Internet have been getting on my nerves lately. Let’s dive in. I was looking for Captain Marvel analysis on YouTube and all I could find was why Captain Marvel didn’t work, how Captain marvel ruined marvel, we don’t need feminism in movies, how Captain Marvel ruined Marvel’s perfect score, blah blah blah. There are like zero to none videos telling about actually how Captain Marvel was great movie.

*Cough* Captain Marvel made over 1 billion dollars but go off I guess.*cough*

I’ll tell you how Captain marvel actually worked?

1. It gave us strong powerful women pilots who work in the air force.

2. It empowered little girls who watched Captain Marvel.

3. It taught all the girls that they don’t have to smile, when a man asks them to smile.(that scene where a man asks carol to smile is a reflection of a woman’s daily experience)

4. It gave us a black strong woman who raised a child as a single mother.

5. It proved that power of love and friendship is unbeatable.(carolmaria)

6. The dynamic duo of Carol and Nick Fury.

7. Goose the cat

8. The subtle humour.

9. You can be wrong. There’s always a room for correction.

10. You don’t have to hide your emotions to be strong.

11. Take control of your lives.

12. It showed us the reality that men are charismatic, but it doesn’t change the fact that they are controlling.

13. It empowered everyone who has felt emotional vulnerability at a point.

14. It empowered young kids to stand up, when they fall down.

15. You don’t always need a male superhero who fights bad guys to empower you, sometimes a cat lady who explores her identity and helps green people is enough.

And you know what actually ruined marvel?

1. Thor 1, Thor 2, Incredible hulk and Age of Ultron(where’s your six page essay about these movies.smh)

2. Joss whedont

3. Hidden rape joke(yes it’s there. here’s the link about the analysis)

4. Whitewashing of characters

5. Making Jewish characters help nazis

6. Sexualzing Black Widow

7. Leaving her only up to being a man’s fantasy

8. Making a woman feel she’s a monster because she’s infertile

9. Setting up BruceNat romance in aou only because they both are monsters

10. Bad action scenes and not at all subtle humour in aou

11. You know what? Everything about aou

12. Not making Clint Barton deaf

13. Not building Sharon Carter’s character (she’s was supposed to be a bigger part of civil war, not only just a kiss)

14. Bad writing in Thor 1 and Thor 2( marvel should be thankful to Taika)

I can go on,,,,,,,,,,,

blog.name: alexandro-lima
blog.title: Alexandro Lima - Ilustrador
blog.description: Olá, bem vindo ao meu blog! Sou um ilustrador/arte finalista publicitário com larga experiência de mercado. Considero como seus “mestres inspiradores” Will Eisner, Jack Kirby, John Buscema e Canini. Sou um apreciador de quadrinhos, utilizo muito desta que é considerada a nona arte como fonte de referência para muitos de seus trabalhos.Mesclo trabalho à mão com vetorização e colorização digital em meus trabalhos. Realizo ilustrações, caricaturas, logotipos e pinturas. Este blog tem o objetivo de mostrar o que mais atual ando produzindo. Divulgue e opine!
